1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 44-04 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to designating certain crash scene images as exempt records; and to
3 amend and reenact subsection 9 of section 44-04-18.7 of the North Dakota Century Code,
4 relating to exempt records related to criminal intelligence and investigation information.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Subsection 9 of section 44-04-18.7 of the North Dakota
7 Century Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
8 9. An image is an exempt record if the image is taken with:
9 a. With a body camera or similar device and which is taken incontains an image of:
10 (1) Nude or partially denuded human figures as defined in section
11 12.1 - 27.1 - 03.1 ;
12 (2) An individual with serious bodily injury as defined in section 12.1 - 01 - 04; or
13 (3) A deceased individual; or
14 b. In a private place is an exempt record.
15 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 44-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
16 and enacted as follows:
17 Crash scene images - Exempt.
18 An image of an individual from a crash scene or incident is an exempt record if the image
19 contains:
20 a. Nude or partially denuded human figures as defined in section 12.1 - 27.1 - 03.1 ;
21 b. An individual with serious bodily injury as defined in section 12.1 - 01 - 04 ;
22 c. A deceased individual; or
23 d. A minor.
